{
    "swagger": "2.0",
    "info": {
        "title": "goboxd API",
        "description": "HTTP service that compiles or interprets untrusted source code inside an nsjail sandbox and runs it against test cases, returning structured per-test results.\n\n**Two execution endpoints:**\n- `POST /run` — the strict contract: `tests` is required, and each test result carries no `exit_code`.\n- `POST /v1/run` — a superset that adds a per-test `exit_code`, raw execution (empty `tests` runs once against `stdin`), and evaluator mode (grade with a custom program).\n\nValidation, security, resource limits, and status semantics are identical across both.",
        "version": "1.0",
        "contact": {}
    },
    "paths": {
        "/healthz": {
            "get": {
                "description": "Returns 200 as long as the server process is running. Intended for load-balancer liveness probes.",
                "produces": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "tags": [
                    "health"
                ],
                "summary": "Liveness check",
                "responses": {
                    "200": {
                        "description": "OK",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.HealthzResponse"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "/info": {
            "get": {
                "description": "Returns build metadata (version, commit, Go version), nsjail info, registered language list with default limits, server-wide enforcement limits, and live runtime statistics (in-flight jobs, totals, disk space).",
                "produces": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "tags": [
                    "health"
                ],
                "summary": "Server info and stats",
                "responses": {
                    "200": {
                        "description": "OK",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.InfoResponse"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "/readyz": {
            "get": {
                "description": "Probes nsjail and every registered language binary. Returns 200 when all probes pass; 503 when any probe fails. Use this for load-balancer readiness probes.",
                "produces": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "tags": [
                    "health"
                ],
                "summary": "Readiness check",
                "responses": {
                    "200": {
                        "description": "OK",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ReadyzResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "503": {
                        "description": "One or more probes failed — service is degraded",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ReadyzResponse"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "/run": {
            "post": {
                "description": "Compiles (if needed) and runs the submitted source against one or more test cases inside an nsjail sandbox.\n\n**Result encoding:** HTTP 200 is returned for all structurally valid requests. Execution outcomes (build failure, wrong output, TLE, MLE, runtime error) are encoded in the `status` fields of the response body — not as HTTP error codes.\n\n**Test cases:** `tests` is required and must contain at least one entry (up to the server's `max_tests`). Each `stdin` feeds the program; `expected_stdout` is compared against its stdout.\n\n**Filename requirements:** Some languages (e.g. Java) require `source_filename` and `artifact_filename` to match the public class name. The language definition's strategy controls this.\n\n**Flag allowlists:** Build and run flags are filtered against a per-language allowlist. Disallowed flags return 400 `invalid_flag`.\n\n**Limit overrides:** Per-request limits may only reduce a language's configured maximum — attempting to exceed the language ceiling returns 400 `invalid_limits`.\n\n---\n\n**Sample request (C++, one test case):**\n```json\n{\n\"language\": \"cpp\",\n\"source\": \"#include <iostream>\\nint main(){std::cout<<\\\"hi\\\";}\",\n\"source_filename\": \"solution.cpp\",\n\"artifact_filename\": \"solution\",\n\"build\": {\n\"limits\": { \"wall_time_s\": 5, \"memory_kb\": 1048576, \"max_processes\": 100 },\n\"flags\": [\"-O2\"]\n},\n\"run\": {\n\"limits\": { \"wall_time_s\": 3, \"memory_kb\": 524288, \"max_processes\": 64 },\n\"flags\": []\n},\n\"tests\": [\n{ \"stdin\": \"1\\n\", \"expected_stdout\": \"hi\" }\n]\n}\n```\n\n**Sample response** (code printed `\"HI\"` instead of `\"hi\"` — wrong_output):\n```json\n{\n\"status\": \"wrong_output\",\n\"build\": { \"status\": \"ok\", \"stdout\": \"\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"duration_ms\": 412 },\n\"tests\": [\n{ \"status\": \"wrong_output\", \"stdout\": \"HI\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"duration_ms\": 38, \"memory_peak_kb\": 8192 }\n]\n}\n```",
                "consumes": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "produces": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "tags": [
                    "execution"
                ],
                "summary": "Execute code in a sandbox",
                "parameters": [
                    {
                        "description": "Code execution request",
                        "name": "body",
                        "in": "body",
                        "required": true,
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.RunRequest"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "responses": {
                    "200": {
                        "description": "Execution completed (check body status fields for pass/fail)",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.RunResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "400": {
                        "description": "Validation error — see error.code for the specific cause",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ErrorResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "500": {
                        "description": "Internal server error (nsjail fault, disk full, etc.)",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ErrorResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "503": {
                        "description": "Server at capacity or request cancelled by client",
                        "schema": {
                            "type": "string"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "/v1/run": {
            "post": {
                "description": "Superset of `POST /run` for richer clients. The contest endpoint is `/run`; `/v1/run` keeps the same request shape and all the same validation, security, limits, and status semantics, and adds three things:\n\n1. **`exit_code`** — every test result includes the process exit code.\n2. **Raw execution** — submit an empty (or omitted) `tests` array to run the program once against `stdin` with no output grading. The single result reports the raw outcome (and `exit_code`).\n3. **Evaluator mode** — supply an `evaluator` program (in any registered language) to grade each test's output instead of comparing it to `expected_stdout`. Each test result then also carries `verdict`, `score`, and `message`.\n\n---\n\n**Sample request (raw execution — no tests, just stdin):**\n```json\n{\n\"language\": \"py3\",\n\"source\": \"import sys; print(sys.stdin.read().upper())\",\n\"stdin\": \"hello\\n\"\n}\n```\n\n**Sample response:**\n```json\n{\n\"status\": \"accepted\",\n\"build\": { \"status\": \"ok\", \"stdout\": \"\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"duration_ms\": 0 },\n\"tests\": [\n{ \"status\": \"accepted\", \"stdout\": \"HELLO\\n\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"exit_code\": 0, \"duration_ms\": 41, \"memory_peak_kb\": 7508 }\n]\n}\n```",
                "consumes": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "produces": [
                    "application/json"
                ],
                "tags": [
                    "execution"
                ],
                "summary": "Execute code (extended: exit_code, raw, evaluator)",
                "parameters": [
                    {
                        "description": "Code execution request. `tests` may be empty for raw execution; `evaluator` enables custom grading.",
                        "name": "body",
                        "in": "body",
                        "required": true,
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.RunRequest"
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "responses": {
                    "200": {
                        "description": "Execution completed (check body status fields for pass/fail)",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.V1RunResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "400": {
                        "description": "Validation error — see error.code for the specific cause",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ErrorResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "500": {
                        "description": "Internal server error (nsjail fault, disk full, etc.)",
                        "schema": {
                            "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ErrorResponse"
                        }
                    },
                    "503": {
                        "description": "Server at capacity or request cancelled by client",
                        "schema": {
                            "type": "string"
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    },
    "definitions": {
        "config.LimitsDef": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "max_processes": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 64
                },
                "memory_kb": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 262144
                },
                "wall_time_s": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 5
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.BuildInfo": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "commit": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "abc1234"
                },
                "go_version": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "go1.26.3"
                },
                "version": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "dev"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.BuildResult": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "duration_ms": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 412
                },
                "status": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "ok",
                        "failed",
                        "internal_error"
                    ],
                    "example": "ok"
                },
                "stderr": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                },
                "stdout": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.ErrorDetail": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "code": {
                    "description": "Code is a stable machine-readable identifier.",
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "invalid_json",
                        "unknown_language",
                        "source_too_large",
                        "missing_source_filename",
                        "missing_artifact_filename",
                        "invalid_filename",
                        "invalid_flag",
                        "invalid_limits",
                        "invalid_test_count",
                        "stdin_too_large",
                        "expected_too_large",
                        "overloaded",
                        "internal_error"
                    ],
                    "example": "unknown_language"
                },
                "message": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "language \"cobol\" is not registered"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.ErrorResponse": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "error": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ErrorDetail"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.EvaluatorSpec": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "/v1/run only. A scoring program that grades each test's output instead of comparing it to expected_stdout. Reuses a registered language and accepts the same per-phase flag/limit overrides as the candidate.",
            "properties": {
                "artifact_filename": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "checker"
                },
                "build": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.PhaseOverride"
                },
                "language": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "py3"
                },
                "run": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.PhaseOverride"
                },
                "source": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "import json,sys; print(json.dumps({\"verdict\":\"accepted\",\"score\":1.0}))"
                },
                "source_filename": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "checker.py"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.HealthzResponse": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "status": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "ok"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.InfoResponse": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "build_info": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.BuildInfo"
                },
                "languages": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "items": {
                        "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.LanguageInfo"
                    }
                },
                "limits": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ServiceLimits"
                },
                "nsjail": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.NsjailInfo"
                },
                "stats": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ServiceStats"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.LanguageInfo": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "default_run_limits": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.LanguageRunLimits"
                },
                "id": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "py3"
                },
                "name": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "Python 3"
                },
                "version": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "Python 3.11.2"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.LanguageRunLimits": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "max_processes": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 100
                },
                "memory_kb": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 102400
                },
                "wall_time_s": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 10
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.NsjailInfo": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "path": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "/usr/local/bin/nsjail"
                },
                "version": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "3.4"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.PhaseOverride": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "flags": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "example": [],
                    "items": {
                        "type": "string"
                    }
                },
                "limits": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/config.LimitsDef"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.ProbeInfo": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "error": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                },
                "ok": {
                    "type": "boolean",
                    "example": true
                },
                "version": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "Python 3.11.2"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.ReadyzResponse": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "languages": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "additionalProperties": {
                        "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ProbeInfo"
                    }
                },
                "nsjail": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.ProbeInfo"
                },
                "status": {
                    "description": "Status is \"ok\" when all probes pass; \"degraded\" when any probe fails.",
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "ok",
                        "degraded"
                    ],
                    "example": "ok"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.RunRequest": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "artifact_filename": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "solution"
                },
                "build": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.PhaseOverride"
                },
                "evaluator": {
                    "description": "/v1/run only. Custom grading program; ignored by /run.",
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.EvaluatorSpec"
                },
                "language": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "cpp"
                },
                "run": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.PhaseOverride"
                },
                "source": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "#include <iostream>\nint main(){std::cout<<\"hi\";}"
                },
                "source_filename": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "solution.cpp"
                },
                "stdin": {
                    "description": "/v1/run raw mode only: stdin fed to the single run when tests is empty. Ignored by /run.",
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                },
                "tests": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "items": {
                        "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.TestCase"
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.RunResponse": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "build": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.BuildResult"
                },
                "status": {
                    "description": "Status summarises the overall result. \"accepted\" means build succeeded and all tests passed.",
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "accepted",
                        "build_failed",
                        "wrong_output",
                        "output_whitespace_mismatch",
                        "time_exceeded",
                        "memory_exceeded",
                        "runtime_error",
                        "internal_error"
                    ],
                    "example": "wrong_output"
                },
                "tests": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "items": {
                        "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.TestResult"
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.ServiceLimits": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "max_concurrent_jobs": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 10
                },
                "max_source_bytes": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 262144
                },
                "max_tests": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 50
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.ServiceStats": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "disk_free_bytes_jail_dir": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 10737418240
                },
                "in_flight_jobs": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 2
                },
                "jobs_failed_internal": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 0
                },
                "jobs_total": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 1042
                },
                "last_internal_error_at": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
                },
                "queue_size": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 0
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.TestCase": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "expected_stdout": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "hi"
                },
                "stdin": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "1\n"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.TestResult": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "duration_ms": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 38
                },
                "memory_peak_kb": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 8192
                },
                "status": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "accepted",
                        "wrong_output",
                        "output_whitespace_mismatch",
                        "time_exceeded",
                        "memory_exceeded",
                        "runtime_error",
                        "not_executed",
                        "internal_error"
                    ],
                    "example": "wrong_output"
                },
                "stderr": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                },
                "stdout": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "HI"
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.V1RunResponse": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "Response body for POST /v1/run. Mirrors RunResponse but each test carries exit_code (and verdict/score/message in evaluator mode).",
            "properties": {
                "build": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.BuildResult"
                },
                "status": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "accepted",
                        "build_failed",
                        "wrong_output",
                        "output_whitespace_mismatch",
                        "time_exceeded",
                        "memory_exceeded",
                        "runtime_error",
                        "internal_error"
                    ],
                    "example": "accepted"
                },
                "tests": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "items": {
                        "$ref": "#/definitions/handler.V1TestResult"
                    }
                }
            }
        },
        "handler.V1TestResult": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "duration_ms": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 41
                },
                "exit_code": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 0
                },
                "memory_peak_kb": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "example": 7508
                },
                "message": {
                    "description": "Evaluator mode only.",
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                },
                "score": {
                    "description": "Evaluator mode only.",
                    "type": "number",
                    "example": 1.0
                },
                "status": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": [
                        "accepted",
                        "wrong_output",
                        "output_whitespace_mismatch",
                        "time_exceeded",
                        "memory_exceeded",
                        "runtime_error",
                        "not_executed",
                        "internal_error"
                    ],
                    "example": "accepted"
                },
                "stderr": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": ""
                },
                "stdout": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "HELLO\n"
                },
                "verdict": {
                    "description": "Evaluator mode only.",
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "accepted"
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
